    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - 9600, 9700, 9800 - REMOVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
            <title>STEERING WHEEL</title>
            <para>The steering wheel can be removed without removing the steering column from the vehicle. Likewise, it
                is not necessary to remove the steering wheel in order to remove the steering column.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the horn button by placing fingers evenly under the lip of the horn button edge
                    and pull up.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the snap ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel nut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel with puller tool ZTSE-4229 or equivalent (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501003">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501003" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501003" filename="../figg05/g0501003.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Steering Wheel Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the retainer slip ring, remove the three pan head screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501004">Figure 4</hotlnk>) and pull the slip ring retainer from the back of the
                    steering wheel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501005">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501004" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501004" filename="../figg05/g0501004.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Retainer Pan Head Screws</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PAN HEAD SCREWS (QTY. 3)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HORN CABLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. NARROW SPOKE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0501005" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501005" filename="../figg05/g0501005.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Slip Ring Retainer (Removed)</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
